19 §2354.11. Premortem interventions; definitions; prohibitions
20 A. For purposes of this Section, "premortem intervention" means any
21 medical procedure, test, medication, cannulation, or other intervention
22 undertaken prior to the determination of death for the purpose of facilitating
23 organ or tissue recovery.
24 B. No premortem intervention shall be performed unless it is medically
25 indicated for the direct benefit of the patient or is performed pursuant to a
26 legally effective consent applicable to premortem interventions, as provided in
27 this Section.
28 C. Regardless of consent, no person shall perform or direct any
29 premortem intervention that has a material likelihood of any of the following:
