5 §2354.12. Post-determination handling and transport of the decedent
6 A. This Section applies following the determination and pronouncement
7 of death under R.S. 9:111 and the recovery of any organ or tissue pursuant to
8 an anatomical gift.
9 B. Prior to the recovery of organs or tissue, the individual authorized to
10 make an anatomical gift, or the individual's authorized representative where
11 applicable, shall be informed in writing of any plan to do any of the following:
12 (1) Transport the decedent from the hospital or facility where death was
13 determined to another facility for further organ or tissue recovery, processing,
14 or handling.
15 (2) Continue mechanical ventilation, perfusion, or other artificial
16 support of bodily functions following the determination of death for purposes
17 related to organ or tissue recovery.
18 C. No transport or continuation of mechanical support described in
19 Subsection B of this Section shall occur unless expressly authorized as part of
20 a legally effective authorization applicable to post-determination handling and
21 transport.
22 D. Authorization to make an anatomical gift after death shall not, by
23 itself, constitute authorization for transport of the decedent to a nonhospital
24 facility or for continuation of mechanical support following death
25 determination.
26 E. Any handling or transport of the decedent following death
27 determination and organ or tissue recovery shall be conducted in a manner
28 consistent with the dignity of the decedent and with the reasonable expectations
29 of the family, as informed by the disclosures made under this Section.
